I once spent half a year abroad in Brazil for an internship. When I had just arrived at the airport and stood there completely lost, a friendly woman offered me a ride into town. On the drive she told me in rather broken english that her daughter was abroad herself and that she hoped that someone would similarly help her daughter, if she needed it.
I liked this thought: that we can help each other, even though half the globe might be between us. And that maybe, in some form or another, this help might even come back to us when we need it.

lender.name: Domenico
lender.occupational_info: It is the World that gives me millions of images, ideas and emotions at every moment. I insinuate myself into temporal space to steal something that is always incredible from the world, something that is unique and that cannot be duplicated, something that has changed that instant into eternity. Men, women and children from all over the world that I have had the fortune to meet have all left me with something. And it is with great humility, the humility that is the only way for me to go, that I interrupted their daily lives. Just for an instant. A moment that meant a flash of freedom for many of them Born in 1974. A freelance photojournalist. 15 years of traveling around the world to understand, discover and learn. The “road” is the only experience that really counts, casual encounters are the most important, dangerous moments are the most exciting. These sensations are so powerful that the “normal” existence you go back to safe and sound seems almost disappointing. We will never be able to possess eternity. It is for this reason that a get I sense of melancholy at every shot, as if that moment that just passed has already been lost, lost forever. I demand a lot from every shot I take: it has to give me back the dream of that moment which life has given to me. It has to be returned forever. I want to live it over again every time I see the shot. It doesn’t happen every time, but when my eyes see what it is they experienced, I gain the strength to seek an encounter with those who – like myself - dream the simplest and greatest dream there is: that of a world filled with brothers.
